, and not as cryptic as <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../494/32494.xml">
vi</link> or ex.</p>
<p>

Diakonos uses the common Macintosh/Windows keyboard shortcuts - Ctrl-C to copy, Ctrl-V to paste, Ctrl-O to open a file, Ctrl-S to save and so on, instead of the more idiosyncratic key combinations used by most other console-based editors.</p>
<p>

Diakonos is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../768/25768.xml">
Ruby</link> program, and hence needs <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../768/25768.xml">
Ruby</link> installed.</p>

